text: Donna G. Nelson (born 1943) is an American Republican politician who served in the Oregon House of Representatives from 2001 until 2009, representing Yamhill County. She previously served as a board member of Evergreen International Aviation. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1943 births Category:Oregon Republicans Category:Members of the Oregon House of Representatives Category:People from McMinnville, Oregon Category:Women state legislators in Oregon Category:People from Paducah, Texas Category:21st- century American politicians Category:21st-century American women politicians
